==English==

===Noun===
'''hardwood''' (''[[countable]]'' and ''[[uncountable]]'')

#''([[countable]])'' (mostly in botany) The wood from any dicotyledonous tree, without regarding how hard this wood is: "'''balsa''' is a hardwood, but a soft hardwood".
#''([[countable]])'' (in more general use) As the preceding but limited to those that are commercial timbers, and are at least average in hardness: '''ash''', '''oak''', etc.
#''([[countable]])'' (forestry) The tree or tree species that yields the preceding: "This hardwood has been planted extensively throughout the hills here."
#''([[uncountable]])'' A joint term for the commercial timbers, without distinguishing which: "You should have used hardwood for this window sill instead of this junk." 

